Health Education Programs

     National Diabetes Education Program (NDEP)

     Weight-control Information Network (WIN)

     National Diabetes Information Clearinghouse (NDIC)

     National Digestive Diseases Information Clearinghouse (NDDIC)

     National Kidney and Urologic Diseases Information Clearinghouse
   (NKUDIC)

National Diabetes Education Program (NDEP)

   The NDEP consists of public and private partners working together to
   improve treatment, promote early diagnosis, and prevent the onset of
   diabetes.
   Go to the NDEP home page for

     * Publications for health care providers and patients
     * Information for the media
     * Public service campaign materials
     * Plans for community outreach programs.

Weight-control Information Network (WIN)

   A national source of information on weight control, WIN produces and
   collects materials on obesity and weight-related nutritional disorders
   and disseminates them to health professionals and the public.
   Go to the WIN page for

     * Publications for health care providers and patients
     * Resources.

National Diabetes Information Clearinghouse (NDIC)

   A service designed to increase knowledge and understanding about
   diabetes among health care professionals, people with diabetes and
   their families, and the general public. Give us your feedback through
   the customer satisfaction survey.
   Go to the NDIC page for

     * Publications for health care providers and patients
     * Resources.

National Digestive Diseases Information Clearinghouse (NDDIC)

   A service designed to increase knowledge and understanding about
   digestive diseases and health among people with digestive diseases and
   their families, health care professionals, and the general public. Give
   us your feedback through the customer satisfaction survey.
   Go to the NDDIC page for

     * Publications for health care providers and patients
     * Resources.

National Kidney and Urologic Diseases Information Clearinghouse (NKUDIC)

   A service designed to increase knowledge and understanding about kidney
   and urologic diseases and health among patients and their families,
   health care professionals, and the general public. Give us your
   feedback through the customer satisfaction survey.
   Go to the NKUDIC page for

     * Publications for health care providers and patients
     * Resources.

